1. What is Simpson's Paradox?
a. A paradox in computer programming
b. A physical phenomenon where associations between variables change when data is combined
c. A statistical phenomenon where associations between variables change when data is divided into subgroups
d. A paradox in geometry

Correct! c
2. In a graphical representation of Simpson's Paradox, what does it look like when there is a reversal of an association between two variables?
a. The lines on the graph intersect
b. The lines on the graph form a straight line
c. The lines on the graph diverge in opposite directions
d. The lines on the graph overlap perfectly

Correct! c
